						               													<description>This started life as a computer game by Ingo Alth&amp;ouml;fer and has been worked into a board game by Reinhold Wittig. The board is in the shape of Easter Island (Rapa Nui) and has 45 spaces. Each player has 2 pieces which are placed on the board. On a turn a piece is moved to an adjacent empty space and a wooden die-holder is then put in the place just moved from. A die is then rolled and put in the holder. After the first 9 moves, each turn also has a second element. This is to remove an empty holder from the board or to roll a die and remove a die from the board with the same number (thus leaving an empty holder). The aim is to be the last player to be able to move.&amp;#10;You need to be able to corner off an area for yourself and also to be in positions where removal of dice will benefit your future movement.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
